<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7626233>
    dc:description "FIGURE 23. A–D, Pitho lherminieri (Desbonne in Desbonne & Schramm, 1867). A, male, cl 5.5 mm, cw 4.8 mm (MZUSP 39685). Left rostral spine broken. Note hooked setae anteriorly. B, Ovigerous female, cl 6.0 mm, cw 5.0 mm (MZUSP 39685), decorated anteriorly with algae. C, D, Ovigerous female, cl 5 mm, cw 4.5 mm (MZUSP 40214). Note large eggs. Habitus dorsal (A–C) and ventral (D) views. Photographs by A. Pol." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7626233/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

